listing_description: Silicon Valley Co-Living Home. You are booking a private bedroom in a 7 bedroom shared home. All guests are staying at least 31 days. The common shared space is a living room with a seating area for conversation and tv viewing. The other shared room is a dining room with a large table for eating and working. The shady backyard has a BBQ and seating for outdoor dining and working. MONTH TO MONTH We can accept longer bookings, but please message us first. You can book 31 days with Instant Book. If you would like to stay longer we can extend this original booking. We will require a month cleaning fee to help keep up the shared space. You will get a room clean and sheet/towel exchange at that point.When you book thru Airbnb, you are booking a short term rental. Your stay is not a tenancy. Keeping stays at 31 days helps establish your stay as a short term stay not a tenancy.MAIL Because this is a short term rental, not a tenancy, you cannot use the house address to receive mail. There are local stores where you can rent mail boxes or receive packages. Often they are inside grocery stores. We will not become involved with any packages that arrive or don't arrive at the house.COVID CHANGES We offer anti-bacterial gel and disinfectant at the entrance and encourage use. We ask that no outside shoes be worn in the home, unless they have been disinfected on the bottom--we provide Lysol spray. We ask all guests to disinfect the bathroom sink area and toilet after they use it. We provide supplies.RESPECT is a huge theme and focus for us. You will be staying with people from various countries with various cultural backgrounds and habits. We ask that you try to keep this in mind. Please be considerate beyond what you might normally be. You never know if something you are doing may be offensive to someone from a different background. Take personal responsibility to clean after yourself and leave a tidy bathroom and kitchen for the next guest.We can guarantee that your bedroom will be 5 Star Clean when you arrive. The rest of the home will be tidy, but since it is a shared space, we can not 100% guarantee the others will clean after themselves.LOCATION: Just off 101 near Central Expressway at Fair Oaks and Arques. Please refer to the map if you are trying to calculate distances. 3 min walk to a shuttle stop for G00gle. I can't list all of the companies that are a short distance from the home: Plug & Play Accelerator, Mercedes Benz R&D, Apple Campuses, Yah00, L1nked1n, Intel, HP, Motorola, Nokia, Synopsis, Symantec, Siemens, Samsung. I most commonly host interns from G00gle, Mercedes, Tesla and various small start ups.VISITORS: This is our Zero Tolerance House Rule. The only people allowed in the home at any time are officially registered guests who have been ID verified. This is for the safety, security and comfort of everyone in the house. You can be assured that your housemate doesn't have a random unknown person in their room and that the house isn't completely overcrowded. If you break this rule Airbnb policy allows for us to cancel your booking without refund.This is not a party house. Your housemates are serious young people who often need to work in the morning. That being said....if you are a several month guest and have a family member or friend accompanying you or visiting you for a a few days, talk to us for permission and guidelines.SECURITY CAMERA: According to Airbnb policy, we want to disclose that we have a Ring Doorbell camera at the front door. It has sound. It will be turned on during your stay. It is a clearly visible camera outside the home. This is for everyone's comfort and protection. We don't have problems in the house, because we take efforts to keep the house safe for you and your things. KITCHEN USE: Using the kitchen is a privilege that is granted to you, if you use it with respect for the others. You can prepare simple meals. No frying fish or cooking with strong spices that leave a lingering odor--what smells good to you may be offensive to others. You are expected to clean up your mess. We do not have cleaning fairies. You must commit to washing your dishes right after use. This means no leaving dishes to soak because you've burned something. If you violate this rule, you may lose kitchen privileges.CLEANING: The cleaning fee that you pay when booking is for preparing the room before your stay and restoring it after you leave. We DO NOT have a daily cleaning service. We have a cleaning person who comes in sometimes. This person maintains the cleanliness of the common area, including the bathrooms, living room and kitchen, but you are expected to clean after yourself. If you would like an additional cleaning, we can arrange it for $40.LAUNDRY: Free on site washer and dryer. You provide your own detergent. Please do not do laundry during the quiet hours because another guest has a bedroom adjacent to the laundry room.CHECKING IN: The house and your bedroom have coded lock. Each guest gets their personal code that works for the front door and their bedroom door. For security, the codes are changed between guests and each guest has a different code.PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION: The house is literally a 3 minute walk to a VTA (55 line) city bus stop. 4 min bus ride to Cal Train. 1 hr, 15 min Cal Train ride to San Francisco. There is a G00gle Shuttle stop just 3 minutes from the house.Lyft and Uber are quick, easy and inexpensive. There are a lot of company shuttles in the area.PARKING: There is a parking spot in the driveway, but this is only available to guests between the hours of 6pm and 8am. Our staff needs it to service the house. It is not assigned to any particular person. Street parking is in front of the house and around the corner on Arques.BIKES: Absolutely no bikes in the house or garage. There is plenty of space in the backyard to store bikes. About half of the guests have a bike.Before you book the wrong place, just know that for things to run smoothly in this type of shared home, we need to run a tight ship. We have rules that we will enforce, so don’t be surprised if we call you out on some violation. We expect a certain standard of behavior from everyone, though we cannot guarantee that everyone will follow the standard we have set. Our only recourse is to cancel the booking of people who violate the house policies. If you feel someone is being disrespectful, you must let us know immediately. We want the opportunity to talk to the other guest and not find out about offensive behavior after your stay has ended.Guest accessYou are renting a private room and you get access to shared space in the home. You can use the living room, dining room, kitchen, laundry, backyard etc. We ask that you respect that it is a shared space.Suggestions:~wipe down all cabinet knobs, refrigerator etc with disinfecting spray and a rag~wear only inside shoes in the house unless you have disinfected them--you can leave all outside shoes near the entry~disinfect the bathroom sink area and toilet after useOther things to note~~Airbnb collects a City of Sunnyvale tax of 10.5% if your stay is less than 31 days. This fee disappears if you book more than 31 days.~~No one can park in the driveway during the hours of 9am-6pm. It is for our staff.~~No visitors at all~~No mail service at the home~~We respectfully request no shoes in the home unless they have been disinfected~~You should disinfect the bathroom after you use it~~Extra cleanings can be booked for $40 per hourRegistration number2017-7717

property_address: Room in Cathedral City, California, United States
listing_description: Planning to accept your next nursing or PT contract in the desert? Why not stay at your own private resort! After long, hard days at the hospital, you'll thank yourself for choosing a home where you can relax in your new luxurious backyard, taking full advantage of the walk-in pool, swim up bar, rock water slide, waterfall and of course the private jacuzzi grotto. Centrally located 10-15 mins from Desert Regional Hospital in Palm Springs & Eisenhower Health in Rancho Mirage!The spaceInside the house, each of our fully furnished bedrooms are bright (blackout curtains available as well), spacious and tastefully decorated. You'll find the mattresses to be high quality, the duvets are fluffy and warm with thick, real down feathers and you'll be sleeping on crisp white hotel quality linens. The comfort and peaceful design aesthetic of the common spaces creates an atmosphere where you can truly unwind. If you enjoy cooking, our fully stocked deluxe kitchen is outfitted with ample counter space, pantry storage and amenities galore.What's the most underrated perk of the house though? The friends you're going to make while staying here! Let's be honest, traveling to a new destination as a working professional can be lonely sometimes. But not here. We make sure to interview each house mate in the home extensively to make sure the vibes in the house will always be the right atmosphere. As travelers ourselves, and having lived in shared homes during many of our traveling experiences, both at home and abroad, we understand the importance of respectful roommates and good company. We do our best to curate your environment, right from the jump, so you can enjoy the best that Palm Springs has to offer, in the company of those you'll enjoy spending time with. Located close to Palm Springs' vibrant downtown, you're a mere 10 minutes away from boutique shops, five-star restaurants and some of the best hiking and golfing in California, as well as the desert's two largest hospitals: Desert Regional Medical Center (Palm Springs), Eisenhower Health (Rancho Mirage), which are both 10-15 minutes drive away.Please note, upon booking, we'll ask to schedule a 1-on-1 video interview so we can get to know you a little bit and confirm that this house is a great fit for all parties involved.We look forward to hosting you :)Guest accessThis property features six bedrooms and three full bathrooms. You will have a private bedroom, and share the communal areas of the home with your fellow house mates.Other things to noteThe house has central AC/heat, and a very large driveway to accommodate all parking needs.

property_address: Private room in home in Sunnyvale, California, United States
listing_description: Silicon Valley Co-Living Home. You are booking a private bedroom in a 7 bedroom shared home. All guests are staying at least 31 days. The bedroom is private but you will share two bathrooms with up to 4 other guests. Two of the bedrooms have a private bathroom. Expect to share the home with young techies and interns. We have fairly strict House Rules. We do this for the safety and comfort of everyone. Be prepared to be uber respectful.The spacePrivate bedroom with a queen size bed, desk,mini fridge, TV. You have equal access to the kitchen, living room, family room, laundry and backyard. There are two full bathrooms in the hallway that are available for your use. Two of the bedrooms have private bathrooms, so generally the two hall bathrooms are shared by up to 4 others.We’ve taken great effort to create a comfortable, convenient home for people visiting the area. The common shared space is a living room with a seating area for conversation and tv viewing. The other shared room is a dining room with a large table for eating and working. The shady backyard has a BBQ and seating for outdoor dining and working. MONTH TO MONTH We can accept longer bookings, but please message us first. You can book 31 days with Instant Book. If you would like to stay longer we can extend this original booking. We will require a month cleaning fee to help keep up the shared space. You will get a room clean and sheet/towel exchange at that point.When you book thru Airbnb, you are booking a short term rental. Your stay is not a tenancy. Keeping stays at 31 days helps establish your stay as a short term stay not a tenancy.MAIL Because this is a short term rental, not a tenancy, you cannot use the house address to receive mail. There are local stores where you can rent mail boxes or receive packages. Often they are inside grocery stores. We will not become involved with any packages that arrive or don't arrive at the house.COVID CHANGES We offer anti-bacterial gel and disinfectant at the entrance and encourage use. We ask that no outside shoes be worn in the home, unless they have been disinfected on the bottom--we provide Lysol spray. We ask all guests to disinfect the bathroom sink area and toilet after they use it. We provide supplies.RESPECT is a huge theme and focus for us. You will be staying with people from various countries with various cultural backgrounds and habits. We ask that you try to keep this in mind. Please be considerate beyond what you might normally be. You never know if something you are doing may be offensive to someone from a different background. Take personal responsibility to clean after yourself and leave a tidy bathroom and kitchen for the next guest.We can guarantee that your bedroom will be 5 Star Clean when you arrive. The rest of the home will be tidy, but since it is a shared space, we can not 100% guarantee the others will clean after themselves.LOCATION: Just off 101 near Central Expressway at Fair Oaks and Arques. Please refer to the map if you are trying to calculate distances. 3 min walk to a shuttle stop for G00gle. I can't list all of the companies that are a short distance from the home: Plug & Play Accelerator, Mercedes Benz R&D, Apple Campuses, Yah00, L1nked1n, Intel, HP, Motorola, Nokia, Synopsis, Symantec, Siemens, Samsung. I most commonly host interns from G00gle, Mercedes, Tesla and various small start ups.VISITORS: This is our Zero Tolerance House Rule. The only people allowed in the home at any time are officially registered guests who have been ID verified. This is for the safety, security and comfort of everyone in the house. You can be assured that your housemate doesn't have a random unknown person in their room and that the house isn't completely overcrowded. If you break this rule Airbnb policy allows for us to cancel your booking without refund.This is not a party house. Your housemates are serious young people who often need to work in the morning. That being said....if you are a several month guest and have a family member or friend accompanying you or visiting you for a a few days, talk to us for permission and guidelines.SECURITY CAMERA: According to Airbnb policy, we want to disclose that we have a Ring Doorbell camera at the front door. It has sound. It will be turned on during your stay. It is a clearly visible camera outside the home. This is for everyone's comfort and protection. We don't have problems in the house, because we take efforts to keep the house safe for you and your things. KITCHEN USE: Using the kitchen is a privilege that is granted to you, if you use it with respect for the others. You can prepare simple meals. No frying fish or cooking with strong spices that leave a lingering odor--what smells good to you may be offensive to others. You are expected to clean up your mess. We do not have cleaning fairies. You must commit to washing your dishes right after use. This means no leaving dishes to soak because you've burned something. If you violate this rule, you may lose kitchen privileges.CLEANING: The cleaning fee that you pay when booking is for preparing the room before your stay and restoring it after you leave. We DO NOT have a daily cleaning service. We have a cleaning person who comes in sometimes. This person maintains the cleanliness of the common area, including the bathrooms, living room and kitchen, but you are expected to clean after yourself. If you would like an additional cleaning, we can arrange it for $40.LAUNDRY: Free on site washer and dryer. You provide your own detergent. Please do not do laundry during the quiet hours because another guest has a bedroom adjacent to the laundry room.CHECKING IN: The house and your bedroom have coded lock. Each guest gets their personal code that works for the front door and their bedroom door. For security, the codes are changed between guests and each guest has a different code.PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION: The house is literally a 3 minute walk to a VTA (55 line) city bus stop. 4 min bus ride to Cal Train. 1 hr, 15 min Cal Train ride to San Francisco. There is a G00gle Shuttle stop just 3 minutes from the house.Lyft and Uber are quick, easy and inexpensive. There are a lot of company shuttles in the area.PARKING: There is a parking spot in the driveway, but this is only available to guests between the hours of 6pm and 8am. Our staff needs it to service the house. It is not assigned to any particular person. Street parking is in front of the house and around the corner on Arques.BIKES: Absolutely no bikes in the house or garage. There is plenty of space in the backyard to store bikes. About half of the guests have a bike.Before you book the wrong place, just know that for things to run smoothly in this type of shared home, we need to run a tight ship. We have rules that we will enforce, so don’t be surprised if we call you out on some violation. We expect a certain standard of behavior from everyone, though we cannot guarantee that everyone will follow the standard we have set. Our only recourse is to cancel the booking of people who violate the house policies. If you feel someone is being disrespectful, you must let us know immediately. We want the opportunity to talk to the other guest and not find out about offensive behavior after your stay has ended.Guest accessYou are renting a private room and you get access to shared space in the home. You can use the living room, dining room, kitchen, laundry, backyard etc. We ask that you respect that it is a shared space.Suggestions:~wipe down all cabinet knobs, refrigerator etc with disinfecting spray and a rag~wear only inside shoes in the house unless you have disinfected them--you can leave all outside shoes near the entry~disinfect the bathroom sink area and toilet after useRegistration number2017-7717

property_address: Entire guest house in Palm Springs, California, United States
listing_description: Tucked in a Cove - and, once the Stagecoach stop for the Old West and the filming location of BONANZA (TV hit series), is our newly-remodeled CASITA. It's 5 min to TOWN; 15 minutes to DWTWN and nestled at the edge of the San Jacinto Mts. The Mt. views here are spectacular! The surroundings feel as though you're tenting at a peaceful campground or a dusty ol’ west ranch mountain community. Not for the fancy : it's made for BUDGET travelers!Access to our popular PS communal home is included.The space* Before requesting your stay, please read this listing description, location, and our reviews. We are a BUDGET friendly Airbnb. This means we cater to college students, artists, hikers, Pet-Friendly people, VAN life travelers and adventure seekers who are not looking to spend hundreds on cleaning fees. We are usually about 90% cheaper than most of the Airbnbs in this area and this market. It's not GLAM, but you'll sleep (hopefully) comfortably. Welcome to the Old West of Palm Springs - a little dusty, a little windy (at-times) and a very secluded mountain home community of people living quietly and peacefully at the edge of the Palm Springs mountains. This area is a former Old West ranch (now called Lazy C Ranch) which was partially divided in the 1960's to accommodate the thriving mobile home trailer communities of desert dwellers. It definitely has the Joshua Tree desert vibes here. In the mornings you can listen to the faint sounds of horses & roosters from the ranch across the street. This modern-casita suite is part of an attached NEWLY remodeled mobile home from the 1960's with its own private entrance. It is located in the San Gorgonio Pass area where high winds can (occasionally) create its own music of enchantment. This casita is connected and affiliated with Jess’s passion and LOVE for the restoration of 1950's and 1960's vintage trailer homes. As such, your reservation will also give you access to Jess’s mini vintage trailer park and main communal home dubbed the Freedom House (It is currently the #1 community home in all of Palm Springs and the pics are included in half of this listing). We've been Super-hosting for more than 10 years. Please read our 900 guests (mostly) 5 STAR REVIEWS about how much AIRBNB guests have enjoyed our vintage trailer park vibe success and our community space to experience the true VINTAGE life of the 1960's - with some modern upgrades of course. Everyone is welcome and of course we’re HUMAN + LGBTQ friendly. This little tiny Casita located 5-min from downtown Palm Springs and 5-min from our RETRO home in Palm Springs. Our casita has MODERN upgrades and is in a no-glam mobile home park community where the scenery of the mountains and its local charm is energetically AWESOME for travelers who want to hit Joshua Tree, hike and are on a budget. Please do NOT book this place if you're looking for the posh and glitz. Did you know Palm Springs was the “jeweled showcase of mobile living” ? Palm Springs had captured the simplified luxury and informal elegance of this latest American phenomenon and this mountain home community was part of that era. So, how did people live back in the 1960’s in these mobile homes? Well, come check it out! This is what Airbnb is all about : discovering NEW places and neighborhoods. We’re honest in saying this is not the glam mobile home park of the elite — YET, it’s the only mountain-mobile home park community that is safe, quiet and allows Airbnb rentals. It’s a unique experience for sure. You’ll see the pics — basic casita with AC, WIFI, and a queen bed/mattress and YES for budget travelers who love saving money and even sleeping on couches . Bathroom, electricity, kitchen, small fridge, and a bed is all you need to go out and enjoy the town! With this booking you will also have access to our main home and Jess’s vintage trailer park 5 min away, which has all the perks (outdoor shower, and community meals and gatherings — etc). Look at our main listing for more details. This is a private space and you will find SOME construction items in the exterior (we are in the process of painting our mobile home and putting in an outdoor space in the future ; aiming for a BLACK exterior ). Prior to booking please know this area is known as the Windy Cove area (hence) it can get WINDY from time to time. It’s also on the footsteps of the Palm Springs mountain so during Spring season the mountains are plush and green AND during the summer it’s a dry beautiful brown mountain vibe scenery. There is a mini-market and gas station within walking distance. No public transportation in this area.Guest accessPlease be respectful of neighbors and this mountain home community.
